p://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Immediately following his third-place finish on Thursday, Lyles was seen laying down on the track on his back.\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.8834116219284065, \"rank\": 0.13184908624938013, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was reportedly given a mask and helped onto a chair for further treatment.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Letsile Tebogo of Botswana won the gold medal with a 19.46-second finish, followed by Kenny Bednarek of the United States at 19.62 seconds.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 628, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.8101984202772209, \"rank\": 0.23426379377863196, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenny Bednarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenny_Bednarek\"}, {\"begin\": 718, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9993360065236381, \"rank\": 0.0006540852909526619, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As you can see in the photo above, Lyles was feeling much better on Sunday, Aug. 4 when he earned the gold medal in the 100-meter final with a time of 9.79 seconds.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.8834116219284065, \"rank\": 0.13184908624938013, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles previously took home a bronze medal at the 2021 Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles told reporters that he does not yet know whether he will be well enough to compete in the 4x100-meter relay, though he's confident in Team USA's chances with or without him.\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9999995360437818, \"rank\": 4.639501533897182e-07, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}]}"